name: V Rev Manchester
directions: Can be found downstairs, head past the bar from main entrance and take a right.
comment: It is written on the wall that these are specifically designed to be single stall, gender neutral and safe.

name: Lima Hall Lobby

comment: Only accessories to Saint Rose Students and Guests, but you don't have to live in Lima.

name: Boiler Room Coffee
directions: To the left and around the corner behind the kitchen

name: Spooked in Seattle
directions: There are two single restrooms that are gender neutral. Sometimes there are gender signs up to reduce confusion with the tourists who would otherwise try relieving themselves in a closet, but no one cares which restroom is used and often they are used interchangeably.
comment: They will ask you to be a paying customer unless you briefly explain your situation (to keep out the vagrant pioneer square population), but they are very lbgtqia+ friendly. If you would like to give back, a couple dollar donation allows you to see the death museum

name: Terry O'reilly's Irish Pub
directions: Walk in the front door of the bar and walk straight back, restroom is on your left.
comment: The bar also has two gendered restrooms in the basement, but the gender neutral upstairs one is far cleaner to begin with.

name: Raising Canes at Boston University
directions: Down a short flight of stairs. Two single user gendered restrooms.
comment: The women's room requires a key kept on the counter to the far right. They plan to change this policy and move to no keys on any restroom.

name: O'Neill Branch - Cambridge Public Library
directions: Need to ask for key. Down the back hall. Don't need to be a 'customer' or otherwise use the library.

name: Travelers thali house
directions: Two unisex bathroom stalls
comment: Pick up a chai to go (delicious), or grab a tiny box of incense for $1. They're friendly and local pops shop, so although they might be ok with someone coming in with an urgent situation, it's nice to support them in return

name: Adele's

name: Adele's

name: Ken Ken Ramen

name: Halcyon Yarns

name: Greater's Ice Cream

name: Gay Goose
directions: Just ask the workers if you can use the bathroom. They will show you where it is. One is accessible, however one is not. The staff there are very friendly.

name: Commotion Consignment
directions: Once through the door, go through the first hall on the right to the back room. Then, go left and the door will be on the left wall in the back. The workers are very friendly and can help you find what you need.
comment: Just browse for a little bit

name: Wise Choice Tack and Trailer
directions: Go in through the door on the side closest to parking, go left. The bathroom will be in a small hallway, but is a good sized bathroom. There will be items that are on hold in the back of the bathroom, and it can be used to change in.
comment: I recommend browsing around a little, and pretend like you know what you are doing there. It is a horse store, so just make them think you are a rider.

name: Beaumont Library
directions: There are restrooms in the front that are multi-stalled, but if you go through the doors and go to the left into the children's section, there will be a single stalled bathroom on your right.
comment: It's a really friendly environment, and since it is just a library you don't have to buy anything

name: target
directions: To the right of the front entrance

name: First congregational united church of christ
Costco
directions: a "family restroom" across the hall from the gendered restrooms

name: Anytime Fitness
directions: At the back of the gym. One disabled, one non disabled. Both Single Stall, gender neutral.
comment: Access is members only, but if you're looking for a gym as well, this is a good option. i'm a non-binary member (look for purple haired mobility scooter user) am always willing to work out with other trans/nb/nc members.

name: Anytime Fitness
directions: At the back of the gym. One disabled, one non disabled. Both Single Stall, gender neutral.
comment: Access is members only, but if you're looking for a gym as well, this is a good option. i'm a non-binary member (look for purple haired mobility scooter user) am always willing to work out with other trans/nb/nc members.

name: Broadway Cinema
directions: To the right of the box office- through the door, behind the lift  (nestled between the lift and the glass double doors)
comment:
Staff are amazing if you need to ask for directions.
Also, it's decorated in vintage shots from films :)

name: Huntly public toilets
directions: Edge of carpark between Nikki's Kitchen and the BNZ bank
comment: 3 public toilets on main street

name: Taco Time
directions: Straight in to the left.
comment: You may need to be a customer.

name: Panera Bread
directions: Both floors

name: Klemzig Interchange
directions: Up the stairs from the o-Bahm track on the northern side.
comment: Public, unisex toilet. Single toilet and baby changing facilities with 10min use timer door.

name: Houston Police Department
directions: Every floor has a single person, non-gendered, ADA accessible bathroom.
comment: You have to check in at the front desk, the building is considered a secure facility. There is an ATM and a small police museum on the first floor, both open to public.

name: McNeal Hall
directions: Basement Level -- Go down the atrium stairs and it is to your left, near the elevator.
comment:
It sucks that it's in the basement, but it exists.
It's a single stall room, pretty big, so you won't have to worry about anyone else coming in.

name: Simon Fraser University
directions:
Above the second bus loop, between the fitness centre and the convocation mall. There are a couple of single stall bathrooms in the covered, but outdoor, hallway. One is near the radio station. 

There are also a couple of single stall bathrooms in the AQ on the main floor.

name: University of Ottawa
directions: 11th Floor bathrooms (Women and Gender Studies Department)
comment: The bathrooms are demarcated as male and female but there is an additional sign stating they are trans friendly.

name: Ben Franklin Crafts
directions: By the fabric
comment: Browse around before using

name: Kum and Go
directions: Left side of building, inside.
comment: Trans and non-conforming friendly staff and company.

name: Unitarian Universalist Fellowship of Midland
directions: There is a single stall bathroom in the basement, a second single stall on the top floor (but a child sized one), and both main gendered bathrooms are known to be for whomever identifies with whichever option.

name: Waterstone's
directions: In the cafe on the lower ground floor (other bathrooms in this store are gendered)
comment: You can easily pretend to be a customer browsing - travel books are on the same floor as this bathroom

name: Cream's
directions: Back of the store. It's the only customer bathroom in the place.
comment: I assume this bathroom is meant for "paying customers", but you can probably get away with not being one. That said, their ice cream is delicious if you're into that sort of thing.

name: Target Broadway
directions: Take the hall to the left of Guest Services, make a right at the locked employee door, and it is immediately to your right.
comment: It's the family restroom, so it's a bit bigger and the door locks from the inside. There's usually no wait.

name: Samaritan hospital
directions: Second floor next to elevators

name: Subject LES
directions: Main Floor Bar
comment: Owners and Management go to great lengths to make this an inclusive open space.
